        <%= link_to image_tag("onemonthrails.png", alt: "One Month Screenshot", class: "img-responsive center-block"), 'http://bit.ly/1zNe4lv', target:"_blank" %><p class="top-buffer-large">The best place to get started with Ruby on Rails development is the <a href="http://bit.ly/1zNe4lv" target="_blank">One Month Rails tutorial</a> by Mattan Griffel. The 8 hours of video tutorial familiarizes you with the basics of the language, introduces you to the development environment, and guides you as you create and deploy your very own clone of Pinterest. One Month Rails is probably the best Ruby on Rails beginner tutorial out there: Google it and you’ll find lots of rave reviews. The course does not assume any prior knowledge. All you need to get started is a Windows, Mac or Linux computer and a solid Internet connection.</p>
